#: ../../W/whack-a-mole.rst:5
msgid "whack-a-mole"
msgstr "whack-a-mole"

#: ../../W/whack-a-mole.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../W/whack-a-mole.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the carnival game which involves quickly and repeatedly hitting the "
"heads of mechanical moles with a mallet as they pop up from their holes.]"
msgstr "[機械仕掛けのモグラが穴から飛び出してくるのを、木槌で素早く繰り返し頭を叩く縁日のゲームから]"

#: ../../W/whack-a-mole.rst:12
msgid ""
"The practice of repeatedly causing spammers' :ref:`throwaway-account`\\s and"
" drop boxes to be terminated."
msgstr "スパマーの\\ :ref:`throwaway-account`\\ やドロップボックスを繰り返し終了させる慣行。"

#: ../../W/whack-a-mole.rst:15
msgid ""
"After sense 1 became established in the mid-1990s the term passed into more "
"generalized use, and now is commonly found in such combinations as whack-a-"
"mole windows; the obnoxious pop-up advertisement windows spawned in flocks "
"when you surf to sites like Angelfire or Lycos."
msgstr ""
"語義1が1990年代半ばに定着した後、この用語はより一般化した用法へと移り、今ではwhack-a-mole "
"windowsのような組み合わせでよく見られる。AngelfireやLycosのようなサイトにサーフィンすると群れをなして湧き出てくる、目障りなポップアップ広告ウィンドウのことである。"
